t in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":37,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnes Higins was born in 1418, in Wolverton, Buckinghamshire, England, her father, Hugh Higins, was 24 and her mother, Henrietta Brenton, was 24. She had at least 1 son with John Jenkes. She died in 1500, in her hometown, at the age of 82."},"et":{"1418–1500":"1418–1500","1414–1459":"1414–1459","1446–1489":"1446–1489","1395–1417":"1395–1417","1395–1418":"1395–1418","1459":"1459","1414":"1414","1446":"1446","1489":"1489","1500":"1500","1455":"1455","after 1418":"pärast 1418","about 1446":"umbes 1446","1395":"1395","1418":"1418","1417":"1417","Wolverton, Buckinghamshire, England":"Wolverton, Buckinghamshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1418–1500":"1418–1500","1414–1459":"1414–1459","1446–1489":"1446–1489","1395–1417":"1395–1417","1395–1418":"1395–1418","1459":"1459","1414":"1414","1446":"1446","1489":"1489","1500":"1500","1455":"1455","after 1418":"1418 jälkeen","about 1446":"noin 1446","1395":"1395","1418":"1418","1417":"1417","Wolverton, Buckinghamshire, England":"Wolverton, Buckinghamshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1418–1500":"1418–1500","1414–1459":"1414–1459","1446–1489":"1446–1489","1395–1417":"1395–1417","1395–1418":"1395–1418","1459":"1459","1414":"1414","1446"